==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English ''[[fraude]]'', from Old French, from Latin ''[[fraus]]'', ''fraudis''.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔːd|-ɔːd]]

===Noun===
'''fraud'''

# An act of deception carried out for the purpose of unfair, undeserved, and/or unlawful gain, esp. financial gain. 
# Such an act injurious to another.
# One who performs such an act.

====Translations====

'''an act of deception'''
*Finnish: [[petos]]
*Spanish: [[fraude]]

'''injurious act'''
*Spanish: [[fraude]]

'''one who performs fraud'''

